# Architecture Split

Manuscript Intel is a Tauri app: **Rust owns behavior**, **Vue owns presentation**.

## Rust (`src-tauri/`)

- File system, scaffolding, discovery, analysis, DB, dialogs, IPC commands
- Business rules (what counts as a chapter, folder layout, validation)
- Prefer new `#[tauri::command]`s over doing work in the UI

## Vue (`ui/`)

- Layout, forms, panels, styling, user interaction
- Call Tauri via `invoke` / composables; render results
- Do **not** reimplement filesystem, parsing, or analysis in the frontend

```typescript
// ❌ BAD — Vue deciding/creating story structure
await mkdir(`${parent}/${name}/Manuscript`)

// ✅ GOOD — Vue collects input, Rust does the work
await invoke('init_story', { request: { name, parent_folder: parent } })
```
